theorem.p:
Let d be a metric on a set X. Then
\mc B=\setBuilder{B_r(x)}{x\in X,r>0}
is a basis for a topology on X.

definition.p:
A Cauchy sequence is a countably infinte set 
\setBuilder{x_n}{n\in\mb N} 
such that for all \epsilon\gt0, the set
\setBuilder{m\in\mb N}{\exists n>m(d(x_m,x_n)\geq\epsilon)}
is finite.
